Hi Everybody,

I am letting users select their own screenmode with a ScreenMode requester,
then opening the selected screen using a taglist.

I am turning AutoScroll on in the taglist, so if the screen is bigger than
the user's display, they can move around over the whole screen.

Well, it works OK on my non-GFX card AGA system - but the question is this:

Since GFX cards don't support screen dragging, I am guessing they don't
support AutoScroll either?

Anyway, it is it going to be a problem opening a screen on a GFX card with
the AutoScroll tag set to TRUE?  Or does the RTG software simply ignore
this tag?

Later...
-- 

