> I am letting users select their own screenmode with a ScreenMode
> requester, then opening the selected screen using a taglist.
> 
> I am turning AutoScroll on in the taglist, so if the screen is bigger
> than the user's display, they can move around over the whole screen.
> 
> Well, it works OK on my non-GFX card AGA system - but the question is
> this:
> 
> Since GFX cards don't support screen dragging, I am guessing they
> don't support AutoScroll either?

Some do, some don't.  It doesn't cause a problem anyway, and if 
you've got a gfx card, you're liable to have a "big enough" display to 
start with.




