This sounds like a dirty contacts type problem with the FPU.  Try removing
it again and cleaning the connections on the socket with meth's and a old
toothbrush!  the same with the pins on the chip.  A quick question for
you...  Does the FPU work when the machine boots from cold and then fuck up
when the computer heats up?  Or is it totally random?  If it is the
former... you may have a Duff FPU!  Get on Powers case :).

<another Snip>

> should leave it in the box.  I have a 40mhz crystal on the Typhoon.

I would leave it in the box!  Well you could take the chance of over
clocking the FPU & CPU... but it will reduce the life of both components!

