@NODE "Mail_209" "Layers"
From: Curt Esser <camge@ix.netcom.com>
Date: Sun, 21 Nov 1999 17:57:25 -0500
Subject: Layers
X-UIDL: 27217104da2cbb57e002ecdf552a3776

Hi All,

I have a program with several windows open.  All have depth gadgets.
The question is, is there a way I can tell how they are arrainged
(depth-wise), or at least which one is currently at the front?

I know it's something in the Layer structure, but I'm not sure how to read
it...

Or, rather, what to read and how to interpret it... 

Thanks.

