@NODE "Mail_304" "PureBasic V1.20 with integrated editor on the way !"
From: Frederic Laboureur <alphasnd@sdv.fr>
Date: Sat, 13 Nov 1999 19:53:33 +0100
Organization: Fantaisie Software
Subject: PureBasic V1.20 with integrated editor on the way !
Encoding: 8bit
X-UIDL: 4c57b7abb42119ea3fad221f68b5fd30

    
    Hello Blitzers, 

>> What happened to PowerBasic?

    Hehe, it's now released. Last public version is 1.10 available on any
Aminet site. Ho, BTW, it's PureBasic now (copyright problem :*D).

    The forth coming 1.20 version will have lot of major improvements:

- Possibility to use any external amiga shared libraries via an GUI
  FD-Convertor :). The produced code is much BETTER than Blitz2 one,
  so using OS function with PureBasic will produce incredibly small
  executable. Number of OS libs are ILLIMITED. No numbers needed, and
  you can decide which version you want to use (ie: V36+, V44+...), within
  the source code.

- Integrated editor ! Like Blitz2, but without the syntax coloring for now.
  Else the compiling is speeded up because all the libraries are loaded once
  at start.

- CLI Compiler still supported...

- New libraries: Sound (Incredibly fast, 20 times faster than the Blitz2 one
  and 100% OS compliant) and Protracker replay.

        Regards, 

-- 

                        Fred.

