Hi Thomas

> Frederic Laboureur wrote:
> 
> >     StooooooP. PowerD is based on AmigaE which already got these
> >     features
> > and of course, it's easy to do that. PureBasic is started from
> > scratch and all must be added, time after time. About multiple
> > return code, just share some variables, and you get it.
> 
> Yes, but then you've got shared variables, defeating the point of
> functions. How about just the ability to return newtypes as well (and
> maybe arrays...).

I agree with Fred. Multiple returned values would be nice, but may be 
too much hassle.

And you shouldn't consider returning a newtype or array (how do you 
fit a newtype or array into a 32bit register? and returning via the 
stack would involve copying loads of data all over the place) that's 
what pointers are for.


