Once you've loaded a font, you can get the nominal width of the 
characters from teh TextFont structure. This should be the width for 
fixed width fonts, and probably either the average, maximum or 0 
width for proportional, I've never checked.

LoadFont 0,"fonts:font.font"
*tf.TextFont = Peek.l(Addr Intuifont(0)+8)
NPrint "Width of font = ",*tf\tf_XSize


