Bippy M churned out *this* drivel:

> okay is it possible for the program to decide whether a$ contains a number
> or a letter simply.. I want to reduce the case "0"-"9" to case x : Do
> something, this is because 0-9 does one thing, and a-z etc does another..
> I tried

Just check a$ before you throw it into the Select routine :

  If Asc (a$) >47 AND Asc(a$) <58
  
    Select a$
      Case BlahBlah
          DoSomething {}
      Case SomethingElse
          WellDoSomethingElseThen {}
    End Select

  EndIf

Any use?
  
