I thought this was because he didn't want Blitz to open the library at the start, but rather when it was needed. AFAIK you can't do this with a "real" blitz library. Also I think I remember being able to free up bsdsocket.library without having that stupid requestor pop up telling you that miami coundn't exit was an issue, this would be another reason why not to put it into a library, since in this sense Blitz libraries are rather restrictive. Once again I might be totally wrong.

