Why do people keep the library open during the init routines?  Why not chuck
in a couple of Open and CloseTCPLib() commands and have the others return an
appropriate error code if if you've forgotten to use OpenTCPLib()
beforehand?  The init routines could open the lib but close them again
straight after (just to check if the lib actually exists) and then you can
also have an IsTCP() command to see whether they need to boot up Miami or
whatknot.

That should give the coder absolute control!

